thankyou_screens.title:
Thank you for sharing your health concern with us. After clicking next, you will be taken to a scheduling page.

Please note: you must have a virtual visit before a home visit can be scheduled.
All done! Thanks for your time.

welcome_screens.title: Hello and thanks for reaching out to your Specialty Healthcare team.  We would like to begin by gathering information on the reason for your visit. You'll be on your way to receiving amazing care in no time.

fields.title: What state do you live in?
What state will you be in at the time of your appointment?
Sorry, Specialty Healthcare is not licensed to treat people in your state of residence and/or current physical location.
If you are experiencing a medical emergency, please call 911 or seek immediate medical attention.

properties.description:
Signs of an emergency may include:

• Active suicidal/homicidal feelings

• Chest pain or heart attack symptoms 

• Significant difficulty breathing

• Stroke symptoms (facial drooping, arm weakness, speech difficulty)

• Severe allergic reaction

• Fever greater than 104.5°F

• Coughing or vomiting blood

• Sudden, severe, uncontrolled pain

• Severe headache

• Loss of consciousness/changes in mental status

• Poisoning/inhalation of substances

• Moderate to severe wounds/burns

• Seizures

• Significant trauma/head injury

•Pregnancy complications (vaginal bleeding, cramping, or abdominal pain)

fields.title: What is the primary reason for seeking care today?

choices.label: A health issue like an illness or injury that is new, started recently (aka "Acute"), and you haven't discussed with a Specialty medical provider in the past (examples include sore throat, cough, urinary symptoms, etc.)

A health issue that you've had ongoing (aka "Chronic") or that you suspect you have that you haven't discussed with a Specialty medical provider (examples include diabetes, thyroid, high blood pressure, depression, anxiety, medication management, etc.)
An update or follow-up on how you are feeling regarding an illness or injury that was discussed with a Specialty medical provider
An update, follow-up or medication refill for a chronic or ongoing condition that you have already been partnering with a Specialty provider to help manage.
A wellness or preventive visit such as an annual physical, wellness coaching, contraception/birth control, etc.
A follow-up visit for continued wellness coaching
A follow-up visit for contraception/birth control
A biometric coaching session/biometric results review
